<br>1) Open up with PA/CD if possible to get the stun. If you dont get it off, you can still win but it will be a bit harder.<br>Try and make use of the reactionary stuns from pierce/thrust/left axe if you cant get CD off<br>2) Poison is important, go with DoT on one hand and enverating on the other.<br>3) Most important! Stay behind them! their spells work on a 180 degree arc. This is the tough part but make heavy use of /stick.<br>4) Switch weapons in mid fight to get a double dose of lethal on them.<br><br>These fights I would say I have won about 3 out of 4, as I will run up against a few minstrels that really know how to play their class well.<br><br>Usually two things will happen when you hit a minstrel<br>1) You open up on him and they immediatly run...if so have a snare poison on hand and work him down from behind.<br>2) You open up on him and he trys to get a bead on you, and you nail him with CD. At this point get your free shots in, switch weapons and STAY BEHIND him.<br><br>There is a third case but I am not going to put it out in plain view for all the lurking Misntrels out there, but its the case where things go bad. <br><br>Keep in mind this is not a sure fire thing, but it will greatly improve your chances. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/umelanu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>melanu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/9/02 6:08:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3713.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Minstrels</span><hr size=1> Nice advice guys thanks<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>I will try this next time.<br><br>Mel. <p></p><i></i>