 + CD off vs. the Inf that when he evades his long stun will give him enough time to kill you.  Considering that the things you will be fighting (primarily other stealthers = Thrust stun, Archers = shield scout, and casters = insta mez/root/stun)... Purge is gonna be the way to go for you regardless of how you think about it.  With resists to effect duration, this may change, but until it does, Purge is gonna be the best point spent... especially if you are solo (which Mythic does not approve of &lt;grin&gt;).<br><br>The advice about staying behind the Minst was good advice, they rarely use stick cause they want to get away from you and CC... (and we all know that speed song classes are spazzes when it comes to running around: &quot;everyone stick to ME, cauz I'm driving this bus!1!!1&quot; = they prolly don't even HAVE /stick on their quickbar).  Hehehe.<br><br>What with pierce you're lucky... I don't bother attacking chain classes with my Slash weps unless I'm higher con or I have some other advantage (they low on End/Insts-used-up/etc.<br><br>Take the Purge now, I don't think you will regret it.<br> <p>Cheers,<BR><BR>Steppin Razor, BORS/Mid [Lvl 42 5-spec SB (mostly good at all, master of none)]<BR>{Appeal to all Infs out there to drop their Buffbot handjobs... you don't need it, not by a mile}<BR>http://www.geocities.com/nage42/Steppin_Razor.html</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/ujayloth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jayloth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/10/02 12:56:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3713.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> What more could you want a stealthing chainwearing insta mezzer?  <br><br>The perfect RvR